{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17644869","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17644869"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:09:09+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:09:09+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18070"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18070","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18070"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.5,0,0.41,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10784"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75380"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10784","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10784"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18070"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60889"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5755"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25138"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25996"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75380","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75380"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 45-year-old woman presents as a new patient to a general practice clinic requesting a prescription for several regular medications. She says she recently moved to the area and the general practitioner does not have access to her past history from her previous clinic. The general practitioner accesses Real Time Prescription Monitoring before making a prescribing decision.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary purpose of Real Time Prescription Monitoring?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Provides electronic prescribing templates","Monitors prescribing patterns of high-risk medicines","Generates automatic repeat prescriptions","Keeps track of remaining repeats for all prescriptions","Records medication administration times"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe primary purpose of Real Time Prescription Monitoring is \u003Cstrong\u003Emonitoring prescribing patterns of high-risk medicines\u003C/strong\u003E. This real-time monitoring system tracks prescriptions for controlled drugs and drugs of dependence to identify potentially harmful prescribing patterns and reduce prescription drug misuse.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProvides electronic prescribing templates\u003C/strong\u003E - This is a function of clinical software systems used for generating prescriptions, not Real Time Prescription Monitoring\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGenerates automatic repeat prescriptions\u003C/strong\u003E - This is a feature of practice management software, not Real Time Prescription Monitoring, as monitored medicines require regular clinical review\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EKeeps track of remaining repeats for all prescriptions\u003C/strong\u003E - This is managed by pharmacy dispensing software and prescription management systems, not Real Time Prescription Monitoring\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERecords medication administration times\u003C/strong\u003E - Clinical charts and electronic medication management systems record administration times, whereas Real Time Prescription Monitoring only tracks prescribing and dispensing events\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EReal Time Prescription Monitoring helps healthcare providers identify doctor shopping behaviour, prescription drug dependence, and unsafe combinations of monitored medicines. This system is mandatory when prescribing certain high-risk medicines including opioids, benzodiazepines, and other scheduled medications.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Real Time Prescription Monitoring tracks prescribing and dispensing of high-risk medicines to prevent prescription misuse and doctor shopping.","Controlled drugs and drugs of dependence require real-time prescription monitoring through Real Time Prescription Monitoring systems.","Healthcare providers must check Real Time Prescription Monitoring before prescribing monitored medicines to identify potentially harmful prescription patterns."],"references":["National real time prescription monitoring. Department of Health and Aged Care. Updated June 2024. Available from: https://www.health.gov.au/our-work/national-real-time-prescription-monitoring-rtpm"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60889"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18070"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60889","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60889"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-29T18:36:17+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-29T18:38:23+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10784"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75380"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","